In recent years, there is been a significant popular topic people have been talking about -government should focus on health care when taxes are provided. While both sides have their point, I will explain the opinions and share why I believe that it is true.

Firstly, the profits for prioritising health care when taxes are provided will increase people from dying from deseases. That is because guru doctors will be sent in when a person is struggling with sickness. By increasing the money, people, espesially elderlies, will not need to wait too long to bring the expert doctors when they need them. By having more economical advantages, it will also cause people in society to try harder to get into the role and increase the doctors. All in all, governments should provide more resources into health care because it is about life, which is precious.

However, governments after changing the priorities will also cause several losses. For instance, developments will be slower, and the quality of kids' education will decrease. In my opinion, life is the most important thing in the world, because there is no second chance. So despite the loss, it is still a winning trade for a longer life and being healthy. People might say, "but the kids' knowledge will be insufficient for grown-ups," but it is still useless when you study with sickness, it will cause less efficient and quality learning than with only a bit of resources gone.

In conclusion, I strongly believe that governments should focus on health care because it affects almost every kind of work that makes this world, such as education, development, and a lot more.
